Class BibtexEntryType

java.lang.Object
  eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.CdmBase
      eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.VersionableEntity
          eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.TermBase
              eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.DefinedTermBase
                  eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.reference.BibtexEntryType
All Implemented Interfaces:
ICdmBase, ILoadableTerm, Serializable
public class BibtexEntryType
extends DefinedTermBase

The class representing types (categories) of BibTeX references (like "article" or "book").

A standard set of BibTeX entry type instances (see BibTeX) will be automatically created as the project starts. But this class allows to extend this standard set by creating new instances of additional BibTeX entry types if needed.

Version:
1.0
Author:
m.doering

ARTICLE

public static final BibtexEntryType ARTICLE()
Returns the BibTeX entry "article": an article from a journal or magazine. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title, journal and year. Optional attributes are: volume, number, pages, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Article subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

BOOK

public static final BibtexEntryType BOOK()
Returns the BibTeX entry "book" (with an explicit publisher). Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author/editor, title, publisher and year. Optional attributes are: volume, series, address, edition, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Book subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

BOOKLET

public static final BibtexEntryType BOOKLET()
Returns the BibTeX entry "booklet": a work that is printed and bound, but without a named publisher or sponsoring institution. Required attribute in BibTeX reference is: title. Optional attributes are: author, howpublished, address, month, year and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Book subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

INBOOK

public static final BibtexEntryType INBOOK()
Returns the BibTeX entry "inbook": a part of a book, which may be a chapter (or section or whatever) and/or a range of pages. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author/editor, title, chapter/pages, publisher and year. Optional attributes are: volume, series, address, edition, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the BookSection subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

INCOLLECTION

public static final BibtexEntryType INCOLLECTION()
Returns the BibTeX entry "incollection": a part of a book having its own title. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title, booktitle and year. Optional attributes are: editor, pages, organization, publisher, address, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the BookSection subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

PROCEEDINGS

public static final BibtexEntryType PROCEEDINGS()
Returns the BibTeX entry "proceedings" of a conference. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: title and year. Optional attributes are: editor, publisher, organization, address, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Proceedings subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

INPROCEEDINGS

public static final BibtexEntryType INPROCEEDINGS()
Returns the BibTeX entry "inproceedings": an article in a conference proceedings. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title, booktitle and year. Optional attributes are: editor, pages, organization, publisher, address, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the InProceedings subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

See Also:
CONFERENCE()

CONFERENCE

public static final BibtexEntryType CONFERENCE()
Returns the BibTeX entry "conference": the same meaning as "inproceedings". This type was introduced in BibTex format only for compatibility with previous bibliographical standards.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the InProceedings subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

See Also:
INPROCEEDINGS()

MANUAL

public static final BibtexEntryType MANUAL()
Returns the BibTeX entry "manual" (a technical documentation). Required attribute in BibTeX reference is: title. Optional attributes are: author, organization, address, edition, month, year and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Generic subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

MASTERTHESIS

public static final BibtexEntryType MASTERTHESIS()
Returns the BibTeX entry "masterthesis" (a master's thesis). Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title, school and year. Optional attributes are: address, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Thesis subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

PHDTHESIS

public static final BibtexEntryType PHDTHESIS()
Returns the BibTeX entry "phdthesis" (a Ph.D. thesis). Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title, school and year. Optional attributes are: address, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Thesis subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

TECHREPORT

public static final BibtexEntryType TECHREPORT()
Returns the BibTeX entry "techreport": a report published by a school or other institution, usually numbered within a series. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title, institution and year. Optional attributes are: type, number, address, month and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Report subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

UNPUBLISHED

public static final BibtexEntryType UNPUBLISHED()
Returns the BibTeX entry "unpublished": a document having an author and title, but not formally published. Required attributes in BibTeX reference are: author, title and note. Optional attributes are: month and year.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Generic subclass of StrictReferenceBase.

MISC

public static final BibtexEntryType MISC()
Returns the BibTeX entry "misc" used when nothing else fits. There are no required attributes in BibTeX reference. Optional attributes are: author, title, howpublished, month, year and note.
This BibTeX entry type corresponds to the Generic subclass of StrictReferenceBase.
